Vice President Kamala Harris welcomed Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and his delegation to the Vice President's Ceremonial Office in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. Harris expressed her joy at finally meeting in person after numerous phone and Zoom conversations. She emphasized the personal and enduring relationship between the United States and Canada, highlighting her own experiences in Canada as a young person. Harris stressed the importance of the partnership between the two nations in the context of North America and their shared allies, emphasizing the significance of their work for the region. Trudeau thanked Harris and expressed his pleasure at being able to meet in person, despite their previous virtual interactions. He emphasized the deep ties between Canada and the U.S., including economic and people-to-people connections, as well as shared values in promoting democracy and inclusivity. Trudeau expressed his excitement about working together to build back better from the pandemic.